# Test 04: Nested Action Inside Thought
# NOTE: <thought> is being deprecated. Nested actions inside <thought>
# are intentionally not parsed. This test documents the edge case.
# When thought is removed, this protocol pattern goes away.
# EXPECTED: FAIL (by design)
<thought>
I need to check the system time and current directory.
<action type="tool" name="system_clock" id="s1" mode="async">
{}
</action>
<action type="tool" name="list" id="s2" mode="async">
{"path": "."}
</action>
</thought>
<thought>
Both results are back. Current time and directory contents received.
</thought>
<response final="true">
It is currently [time] and the directory contains [files].
</response>
---EXPECTATIONS---
events: THOUGHT, ACTION, ACTION, THOUGHT, RESPONSE
actions:
  - name: system_clock
  - name: list
complete: true
